VALUES (1, 'paghetti Bolognese', 'Lunch', 'vegitarian_Non', 'Classic Italian pasta dish with meat sauce.', '1. Cook pasta according to package instructions.\n2. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.\n3. Add minced garlic and onion, cook until softened.\n4. Add ground beef, cook until browned.\n5. Stir in crushed tomatoes, tomato paste, and seasonings.\n6. Simmer sauce for 20 minutes.\n7. Serve sauce over cooked pasta', '500g spaghetti pasta\n400g ground beef\n1 onion, diced\n2 cloves garlic, minced\n1 can (400g) crushed tomatoes\n2 tbsp tomato paste\n2 tbsp olive oil\n1 tsp dried oregano\n1 tsp dried basil\nSalt and pepper to taste', 'Calories: 450 per serving\nProtein: 25g\nFat: 15g\nCarbohydrates: 50g', '200', '4');
